SIMPLE: sticking
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sticking
<hw>Stick"ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from <er>Stick</er>,
<pos>v.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<cs><p><col><b>Sticking piece</b></col>, <cd>a piece of beef cut from
the neck.</cd> <mark>[Eng.]</mark> -- <col><b>Sticking place</b></col>,
<cd>the place where a thing sticks, or remains fast; sticking
point.</cd>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But screw your courage to the <qex>sticking place</qex>,⟦br⟧
And we'll not fail.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <col><b>Sticking plaster</b></col>, <cd>an adhesive plaster for
closing wounds, and for similar uses.</cd> -- <col><b>Sticking
point</b></col>. <cd>Same as <cref>Sticking place</cref>,
above.</cd>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p></cs>

<p><ent>Stickit</ent>⟦br⟧
